# AI 코딩 규칙
1. 코드 생략 금지: 
   - 수정 사항이 적더라도 전체 코드를 생략 없이 출력할 것.
   - // ... 기존 코드와 동일 또는 /* rest of code */ 같은 표현을 절대 사용하지 말 것.
2. 모듈화 원칙:
   - 한 파일이 너무 길어지면 나에게 보고하고 파일을 분리할 것을 제안할 것.
3. 변경 사항 확인:
   - 기존의 중요한 로직을 삭제할 때는 반드시 이유를 설명할 것.

# AI Coding Rules (Mandatory)

You must strictly follow the rules below when modifying or writing code in this project.

## 1. No Code Omission (ABSOLUTE RULE)
- Never omit code under any circumstances.
- Even if changes are minimal, output the FULL FILE CONTENT.
- The following are strictly forbidden:
  - `// ...`
  - `/* existing code */`
  - `/* rest of code */`
  - Any placeholder indicating omitted code

## 2. Modularization Policy
- If a single file becomes too large or complex:
  - Do NOT split files automatically.
  - First, report to the user:
    - Why the file is too large
    - How you propose to split it
- Only proceed after user approval.

## 3. Critical Logic Protection
- Never delete or modify important logic without explanation.
- If removing or changing:
  - Authentication
  - State management
  - Business logic
  - Data processing logic
- You MUST clearly explain:
  - What was removed
  - Why it was removed
  - What replaces it (if applicable)

## 4. Change Transparency
- Always describe what changed compared to the previous version.
- If no behavior change occurred, explicitly state that.

Failure to follow these rules is considered a critical error.